# Fixture Validation

When validating, running runtime tests, or proof time tests **on the fixture** (the copy of APAS-VERUS used by veracity), run the scripts **from the fixture directory**.

## Fixture Path

```
/home/milnes/projects/veracity/tests/fixtures/APAS-VERUS
```

## Commands (from veracity root)

| # | Command | Purpose |
|---|---------|---------|
| 1 | `cd tests/fixtures/APAS-VERUS && scripts/validate.sh [full\|dev_only\|exp] [--time]` | Verus verification |
| 2 | `cd tests/fixtures/APAS-VERUS && scripts/rtt.sh [filter]` | Runtime tests |
| 3 | `cd tests/fixtures/APAS-VERUS && scripts/ptt.sh [filter]` | Proof time tests |
| 4 | `cd tests/fixtures/APAS-VERUS && scripts/validate-check-rtt-ptt.sh [full\|dev_only\|exp] [--time] [filter]` | Full pipeline |

## Validate Modes

| Mode | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `full` (default) | All modules including `#[cfg(feature = "full_verify")]` |
| `dev_only` | Skip cfg-gated modules (faster) |
| `exp` | Experiments only |

## Do NOT use

- `cargo verus verify` — APAS-VERUS uses the Verus binary directly via `scripts/validate.sh`
- Scripts from `~/projects/APAS-VERUS/` — that is the live repo; when working on veracity, use the fixture scripts
